00:00:08.437 --> 00:00:10.865
Today we will make cabbage parantha.

00:00:11.178 --> 00:00:16.765
Let’s see what all ingredients are required for making cabbage parantha.

00:00:17.677 --> 00:00:20.677
Wheat flour - 3 cups

00:00:21.038 --> 00:00:23.649
Cabbage - 250 grams

00:00:24.136 --> 00:00:27.056
Red chilly - less then ¼ tsp

00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:29.798
Coriander powder - ½ tsp

00:00:30.229 --> 00:00:32.594
Cumin seeds - ¼ tsp

00:00:33.057 --> 00:00:36.390
Ginger - ½ inch piece (grated)

00:00:36.768 --> 00:00:39.229
Mango powder - ¼ tsp

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:42.994
Garam masala - less then ¼ tsp

00:00:43.218 --> 00:00:49.413
Salt - ¾ tsp (to add in dough and add in cabbage)

00:00:49.790 --> 00:00:52.369
Green chilly - 1 (finely chopped)

00:00:52.865 --> 00:00:55.230
Green coriander - 1 tbsp (finely chopped)

00:00:55.476 --> 00:00:57.023
Oil- to make paranthas

00:00:58.394 --> 00:01:01.902
Knead dough for making paranthas.

00:01:05.060 --> 00:01:10.587
Add ½ tsp salt and 2 tsp oil in flour.

00:01:17.358 --> 00:01:18.389
Mix well.

00:01:22.571 --> 00:01:25.515
Add little water at a time and knead dough.

00:01:26.610 --> 00:01:32.782
We use half the amount of water then flour.

00:01:33.832 --> 00:01:43.015
Keep aside the dough for 20 minutes so that it gets set.

00:01:54.298 --> 00:01:59.370
Meanwhile prepare stuffing for paranthas.

00:02:21.911 --> 00:02:27.361
Add 2 tsp oil and cumin seeds in preheated pan.

00:02:30.119 --> 00:02:31.952
After sautéing cumin seeds for while

00:02:36.307 --> 00:02:38.307
add coriander powder

00:02:41.934 --> 00:02:42.934
green chilly

00:02:44.874 --> 00:02:45.683
ginger

00:02:52.625 --> 00:02:54.521
cabbage

00:02:59.869 --> 00:03:01.012
 mango powder

00:03:04.064 --> 00:03:05.176
 red chilly

00:03:06.853 --> 00:03:08.115
garam masala

00:03:09.959 --> 00:03:10.784
 and salt.

00:03:14.011 --> 00:03:16.646
Mix all ingredients really well.

00:03:17.633 --> 00:03:20.745
Sauté cabbage for 2-3 minutes

00:03:24.894 --> 00:03:27.029
Start making paranthas.

00:03:27.733 --> 00:03:33.505
Take little amount dough and make round ball.

00:03:36.510 --> 00:03:39.018
Dust with dry flour.

00:03:41.896 --> 00:03:44.777
Roll into 2-2.5 inch diameter parantha.

00:03:52.009 --> 00:04:00.676
Spread some oil on the top and layer 2 tsp stuffing.

00:04:08.170 --> 00:04:12.750
Lift paranthas from all sides and close it.

00:04:14.539 --> 00:04:22.713
Press it gently so that stuffing spread evenly all around.

00:04:23.733 --> 00:04:29.098
Dust the stuffed ball with dry flour.

00:04:30.057 --> 00:04:32.994
Roll it gently.

00:04:37.597 --> 00:04:39.962
Dust again with dry flour.

00:04:44.883 --> 00:04:50.494
Roll into 6-7 inch diameter parantha.

00:05:04.678 --> 00:05:11.190
Spread some oil on the tawa and place parantha on the tawa

00:05:24.777 --> 00:05:27.428
Parantha is roasted form beneath now flip the sides.

00:05:27.861 --> 00:05:29.575
Let it roast from other side as well.

00:05:55.220 --> 00:06:06.407
Paranthas is roasted from other side as well now spread some oil on the parantha and flip the side.

00:06:09.532 --> 00:06:15.735
Spread some oil on this side as well.
Press the parantha gently.

00:06:34.350 --> 00:06:42.937
Roast parantha on brown and medium flame until it gets brown from both sides.

00:06:49.311 --> 00:06:56.896
Parantha is ready; take it off from flame and place of bowl kept above plate or napkin paper.

00:06:57.527 --> 00:06:59.876
Crusty cabbage paranthas are ready.

00:07:00.156 --> 00:07:08.050
Serve paranthas with aloo tamatar sabzi, raita, chutney, pickle or any sabzi you like eating

00:07:08.664 --> 00:07:15.621
Try making cabbage parantha and share your experiences with us.

